Data Scientist		TripAdvisor		Needham, MA		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">We are looking for an exceptional data-driven individual to join our Yield Management group. The successful candidate will report to Director of Yield Management in the Global Sales organization and will be responsible for optimizing existing monetization strategies and identifying new revenue growth opportunities. Located in our Needham HQ office, this role will be focused on driving the analysis of our CPC and CPM campaigns and coming up with new models and algorithms to grow our revenue. This is a tremendous chance to make largest travel site in the world even better, while enjoying the energy and rapid pace of a startup. This role requires very strong emphasis on data analysis and ability to clearly communicate key findings to business audience.<br /><br />Key areas of responsibility:<br /><ul><li>Perform data analysis to support key decision making and evaluate opportunities for revenue optimization.</li> <li>Develop analytical models to improve traffic monetization </li> <li>Provide advanced analytical support to Global Sales organization</li> <li>Conduct rigorous testing of new algorithms and monitor their performance on the ongoing basis</li> <li>Partner with Product Management and Engineering to create product requirements and specification documents for new features and products<br /></li></ul>Qualifications:<br /><ul><li>A results-oriented person who thrives on data and measurements. </li> <li>Ability to derive practical solutions to business problems from not-always-perfect data of formidable size.</li> <li>Experience with translating business needs into data-driven models.</li> <li>You must be comfortable with explaining complex analytical issues to a non-technical audience. </li> <li>Demonstrated proficiency in data transformation, cleansing and interpretation.</li> <li>Strong SQL skills and experience with Big Data stack (Hadoop/Hive/Pig/Spark/…).</li> <li>Masters/Ph.D. in quantitative field.</li> <li>2+ years of experience desired</li> <li>Proficiency with statistical programming environment (e.g. R, Python).</li> <li>Strong problem solving and analytical skills. Demonstrated pragmatic approach to business problems.</li> <li>Ability to work well with colleagues across multiple global offices.</li> <li>Comfortable with multi-tasking in a very fast-paced work environment.</li> <li>Experience with online auctions, A/B testing, digital advertising, or marketing analytics is a big plus.<br /></li></ul>As part of our dedication to the diversity of our workforce, TripAdvisor is committed to Equal Employment Opportunity without regard for race, ethnicity, gender, protected veteran status, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or religion.<br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">TripAdvisor® is the world's largest travel site*, enabling travelers to plan and book the perfect trip. TripAdvisor offers advice from millions of travelers and a wide variety of travel choices and planning features with seamless links to booking tools that check hundreds of websites to find the best hotel prices. TripAdvisor branded sites make up the largest travel community in the world, reaching 340 million unique monthly visitors**, and more than 225 million reviews and opinions covering more than 4.9 million accommodations, restaurants and attractions. The sites operate in 45 countries worldwide. TripAdvisor also includes TripAdvisor for Business, a dedicated division that provides the tourism industry access to millions of monthly TripAdvisor visitors.<br /><br />TripAdvisor, Inc. (NASDAQ: TRIP) manages and operates websites under 24 other travel media brands: www.airfarewatchdog.com, www.bookingbuddy.com, www.cruisecritic.com, www.everytrail.com, www.familyvacationcritic.com, www.flipkey.com, www.thefork.com (including www.lafourchette.com, www.eltenedor.com, www.iens.nl, www.besttables.com, and www.Dimmi.com.au), www.gateguru.com, www.holidaylettings.co.uk, www.holidaywatchdog.com, www.independenttraveler.com, www.jetsetter.com, www.niumba.com, www.onetime.com, www.oyster.com, www.seatguru.com, www.smartertravel.com, www.tingo.com, www.travelpod.com, www.tripbod.com, www.vacationhomerentals.com, www.viator.com, www.virtualtourist.com, and www.kuxun.cn.<br /><br />*Source: comScore Media Metrix for TripAdvisor Sites, worldwide, December 2014<br /><br />**Source: Google Analytics, average monthly unique users, Q1 2015</div>